Kali Malone & Drew McDowall share a two-hour mix for NTS in celebration of their new album Magnetism, out November 7 on Ideologic Organ. The selection drifts through drone, minimalism, ambient, electroacoustic, folk, and sacred music, featuring many friends and collaborators whose work continues to shape and inspire them. The first half features Kali’s selections, with Drew taking over in the second.

nts2.d: There’s a kind of stillness that appears suddenly, like a flash revealing what I had overlooked. As soon as I reach it, it seems to dissolve, yet it keeps shaping the way I listen to the world. In that space where time loosens and sounds lose their names, I looked for a calm that wasn’t escape but presence. This mix was born after a period of relentless noise, when I rediscovered the relief of silence and the gratitude for every fragment of peace regained.
Quiet nostalgia and gentle mise-en-scène curated by a film obsessed curtain maker.

subtle.d: Following his widely acclaimed breakout moment winning the 2013 DMC World Online Championships, Jon1st quickly built an international reputation as a ‘DJ’s DJ’. Not only proving himself as one of the world’s most diverse and musical turntablists, Jon also established himself as an on the pulse club DJ mixing across the alternative bass music spectrum and as an in demand live performer around the world, as well as recording acclaimed guest mixes for everyone from DJ Mag to Boiler Room to Ninja Tune’s Solid Steel to Mary Anne Hobbs to Keep Hush.

subtle.n: CHUFFED 010 w/ David Lunch b2b EMMALINE

subtle.d: Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.
Hailing from Belfast but making moves in Nottingham, Nikki O is a DJ and radio presenter whose sets blend 4/4 rhythms, breakbeats, and the bassier side of techno.
